 Bitcoin Mining

What is Bitcoin Mining?
Bitcoin mining is the process of creating new bitcoin by solving complex mathematical puzzles.
Mining helps to:
•	Verify the legitimacy of transactions
•	Include the verified transactions into a block
•	Reach consensus among all active nodes (so everyone agrees on one correct chain)
•	A new block is added to the blockchain.once theconsensus is achieved.
Because bitcoin has limited supply, mining creates scarcity → demand ↑ → price ↑
(Example: Gold, Crypto)
Block reward might reduce over time due to Bitcoin Halving.
________________________________________
Step 1: Transaction Verification and Inclusion
•	Each node that receives a transaction copy verifies the transaction.
•	All validated transactions are stored in a mempool.
•	Miners then bundle these transactions into a candidate block.
Example:
A → B → C
A sends 2 BTC to C, etc.
________________________________________
Step 2: Proof of Work (PoW)
1.	Miners start looking for a nonce value to generate a block hash that requires ceryain leading zeros.
2.	Miner constructs the block → Block header includes:
o	Version
o	Merkle root
o	Previous block hash
o	Difficulty target
o	Nonce
o	Timestamp
________________________________________
Step 3: Creation of New Block
•	Once a miner creates a valid block, it is added to the blockchain network.
•	Existing chain + New block = Extended chain
________________________________________
Orphan Block
When two valid blocks are mined at the same time and broadcasted:
•	Only one block gets accepted to the main blockchain.
•	The rejected one becomes an Orphan Block.
•	Miners do not get rewards for orphan blocks.
